emotes.msg: Level_40-999
What a foul creature. I have no interest in this!
What a nasty little thing! Enough with the show and tell, you can have it back now!
That's great! Now get it out of my face!
I'm not a collector of skulls! What kind of collector do you take me for?
Wonderful! Maybe I can make this into a drinking mug for you! Then again, maybe I'll just give it back to you and forget I ever saw it!
I have no need for a broken mask.
You probably want to give this to the Olthoi Hunter in Arwic. Perhaps she'll be able to do something with it.
You can't decorate your own?
Just find a carving or whittling knife and go at it!
Wha... that's HUGE! Where did you find that? Be careful when you carve or whittle that, it must be worth a fortune! Unfortunately, I don't buy produce.
Sorry, I'm not going to wear this around town!
There's no way I'm going to wear this!
I wonder if this would fool a banderling.
Thanks for sharing this with me.
Oh! Scary!
Not a bad looking mask.
Something about this mask creeps me out...
Ah yes, the Golden King. Exquisite! What a fine mask this is.
Hmmm, the Assassins Mask, I bet this is nice to have when the desert is restless.
Oh, the Ogre Mask. Somehow the crafter captured beauty in it's ugly features.
King Pwyll looks even more regal in this version of the mask.
You know, this mask is likely to keep people at a distance. No one likes to stand to close to an Assassin.
The mask of the Ogre Magi! I love this mask, but I keep mine locked up at night so I can sleep.
It's as if I'm looking upon King Pwyll himself! Amazing that Alexander could make this from memory.
The Shagar Zharala could have made this. It's a perfect recreation.
Ah!!! A monster!
Oh, hehe, just a mask of Koji's demon. It looks like it's watching me...
Have you a drudge charm, swamp stone, rat tail, or such? I'll pay you good money or items if you give them to me. They're hard to come by.
Did you know there are other people who collect other items, like gromnie teeth?  You might find them in some towns.  I'll take them, but I won't pay you for them!
Very rarely, you can get a perfect red phyntos wasp wing.  If you can give one to me, I'll pay you for it.  I will also pay you for the tails of rats.
I'm particularly interested in the spine of the sandy armoredillo.  Get that to me and I'll give you a health potion.  I'll also pay the same for swamp stones and the scalps of banderlings.
There are others who will reward differently for the same items I collect.  Not all types of monsters carry trophies, and of those variants that do, it's very rare.
Hold on, I'm getting your money.
Keep those rat tails coming!
Another tan rat tail...
Tan rat tails make great boot laces.
Ah, one russet rat tail...
Here you go.
They say grey rat tails are good for the spleen.
Here's your money.
Brown, not bad. I'll get your money.
Here you are, don't forget I have higher rewards for black and red rat tails.
Oooo, this deserves more than a coin reward!
That's the Top Rat reward. I always need more black and red rat tails.
Red! Very good, you get the Top Rat reward for this!
Thanks, hmmm, I think I'll have sausages tonight.
I've been seeing a lot of these...
Here you go.
Hold on, I'm getting your money.
Next time, see if you can find a blue wasp wing.
Ah, a blue wasp wing!
Thanks, here's your reward.
You found one! I don't see many of these around here...
Here's your reward.
These are my favorite and they are hard to find.
Jingle jingle, eh?
Such a pretty looking wing!
More wings, more coin.
White like the snow. So beautiful, but so dangerous.
And I'll pay the same for more of these.
Let's see, Sandy Spine...
I buy all of the Armoredillo spines.
Spine, bronze... mhmm, here you go.
Find me some Island Spines if you can.
It's a trade then. Here are your potions.
May your magic never fail you friend.
Shore Spine, those are pretty good.
You like fighting on the beach? Don't forget your towel.
Oh wonderful, an Island Spine! These are really useful.
Come back with more, please!
Oh wonderful, a new spine! These are really useful.
Come back with more, please!
Oh wonderful, a new spine! These are really useful.
Come back with more, please!
I really love these trinkets. I wonder what meaning they have for the drudges.
Good luck in your travels.
Set that on the leather blotter there while I gather your rewards.
One less banderling causing trouble.
A rare Swamp Stone. Let's see, the going rate is 20.
To your health friend.
Hrm, this is rather fascinating!  Well, I think I can work with this a little...
Ah hah!  Here you go, I had some left over Golem Jo's one of my shopkeeper friends gave to me.  That seems to do the trick.
Hrm, this is rather fascinating!  Well, I think I can work with this a little...
Ah hah!  Here you go, I had some left over Golem Jo's one of my shopkeeper friends gave to me.  That seems to do the trick.
This towel is filthy! But, I can always use a towel.
Always know where your towel is.
Yes, I take those. Towels are incredibly useful.
I wonder who F.P. is.
Right, just set that there and I'll get your reward.
You've got real guts my friend.
I take it the lugian didn't need this?
Thanks! Watch for flying rocks.
My bowyer customers will be pleased.
Remember, some Lugians are our friends.
A sclavus tongue, put it in the jar and I'll get your money.
It'ssss a pleasure doing business with you.
I get a lot of these keys.
I buy all three shadow keys. Let others know.
Ah, not everyone can battle shadows.
There you go.
Good find, these keys are worth a lot.
Here, tradenotes take up less space.
Ah, the mysterious seal of the undead.
A pleasure trading with you.
Hey! I remember my first Red Letter.
Here, have this in exchange.
An Explorer Society Gold Letter. A real collectors item.
This should be a fair reward.

If you had told me a few years ago that we'd someday find that the charms worn by drudges held magical affinity, I would have thought you to be a madman. It take a simple twist and then the magic begins to flow.
I've seen more and more of these coming in lately. They have no magical strength to them, but I like collecting them nonetheless. I don't mind parting with a fair sum for these.

Where this comes from and how it gets left behind after the defeat of the phantasm remains a mystery. So too, the process for creating this potion. But deep in Xarabydun the potion can be created, and has been.    I'd be wary of using such a potion too often.
Ah, a beak from the most feared and troublesome penguin. Wave one of these at Lorca Sammel. I promise you, it's a good time.
Want to hear a joke? Yeah, of course you do. Why did the penguin cross the road?
To go with the...
Collector's shoulders shake with laughter.
Oh no, I just can't say it. I can't. I'm sorry.

Those Ruschk are capable of marvelous feats of engineering, are they not?
Ooh, another Ruschk Ice Shard. Did you know that Ruschk-forged ice does not melt? What I'd give to know why.
The more I learn about the Ruschk, the more curious I am about them.
Did you know that they did not come here through the portals? They're one of the few creatures that are actually native to this world.
They act like savages, but something tells me a fierce intelligence lies behind those eyes.
What an incredible specimen. I haven't seen very many of these. Thank you.
I wish we could strike up some sort of alliance with the Ruschk. They would make excellent allies in battle.
Well, that's nice and disgusting.
Looks like one of the Bloodless found his way into an Eater den, huh?
Virindi? Here? That's odd.
What in the world? Where did this thing come from?
Well, I suppose now we know which one wins in a fight, huh?
As much as I support the Viamontian ideal, I still shudder when I think of what King Varicci did to those Lugians.
Oh dear.
Hey, I think I know this guy.
It's good to slay these things when they're young. Good job!
This leg is huge! I'm impressed that you could slay such a creature.
